@node part19 "System Exclusive (SYSEX)"

-How to record system exclusive ?

° Simple, first check that the sysex flag in the midi-filter-page is enabled.
° Hit the record button and seclect Record, no loop recording please.
° Transmit Sysex messages with your synthesiser, all messages will be recorded until
  you stop recording.
  
  Please keep in mind that sysex messages needs lot's of midi-events, so before you 
  start Dominator, allocate a high volume of events.
  Each midi-event has the possibility to contain a maximum of 7 sysex bytes. 
  Longer messages are internally broken-up. Do not quantize tracks which includes
  sysex data, you could mess-up the data contained in the message !.
  
-How to play it ?

° If you previously had recorded some sysex-events, hit the play-button to transmit the
  data.
  It's nice to know that SMF-midi-files with sysex data can be imported and transmitted,
  most commercial sound-banks or patches for synthesisers can be uploaded this way. 
  
-How to view it ?

° Go to the track-window and select Sysex instead of velocity. The first few bytes of
  every Sysex message will be printed on screen.
  
- What's the use of it ?

° Most systhesisers have the option to dump there voice/patch and/or bank data thru midi,
  via the sysex protocol. Check your synthesisers manual for more information about
  this. Some synthesisers even enables you to change parameters in real-time via sysex,
  ex. the Roland Juno 106.  
  
° The best way to make use of it is to record the sysex data in a seperate track.
  After recording, place a part with the same duration as the sysex-message in the song,
  mute that track. It's best to place the part before the start of your song.
  Every time you need the sysex-data, un-mute the track and play it. Since your song
  starts after the sysex-data, the song will not interfere with the sysex data.  
@endnode

@node part20 "Technical Information"

    - 250 Multi-channel midi tracks
    - Easy GUI with Parts/Events Window in living color.
    - MIDI-mixer with assignable midi-channels and controllers
    - Imports Music-X songs
    - Import/Export Standard Midi Files (Type 0 & 1)
    - Supports standard Amiga Samples
      Samples react to MIDI note/velocity, program-change and pitchbend events.
      (You can have 8 channels of Amiga sound if you link two Amiga's up via MIDI)
    - Program/bank selected window
    - Real-time editing of events
    - Uses locators
    - Able to record & save Sysex messages
    - Runs from kickstart 2.04 and higher.
    - Needs a minimum of 1.5 MB of memory. (1 Meg free memory)
    - Engine uses Running Status and was build from the ground up, completly written
      in C with porting to the AMIGA POWERPC in mind.
    - Updates are freely available on the Internet (AMINET)
     
@endnode
